reviews.text:
If you like the taste of Chinese medical, Noodleholic (aka Mian Guan Huang) should be a restaurant for you.  As their noodle with rich taste of Chinese medical smell.
But the tables here are packed, you don't even have enough space for your dishes to fit into the table.  And the restaurant is always full during lunch peak time, expect to queue outside and wait for your table
Tasty Chinese noodles. The broth was infused with Chinese herbal flavour served pipingly hot which is perfectly soothing on a cold winter day. Will try their signature spicy chicken (口水雞).

The environment is quite dirty and their noodle is ok. Terrible service ever in my life. Especially one of employees is so damn rude. I was having lunch and suddenly she took my food and moved it to the other table. She didn’t even ask me or get permission from me. I understand you want to serve more customers and earn more money. But treat your current customers properly first. I totally lost my appetite because she treated me like sh*t.

The spicy chicken was very salty due to the excess soy sauce in their recipe. 

The peanut chicken noodle...too much peanut sauce and it was very viscous and didn’t go down easy.
Terrible service! The big woman cheat money when she calculating(with the calculator) Please be careful!
